731854f-a.title: Hospitals - Bellevue Hospital - [The morgue building.]
731854f-a.text:
Bellevue Hospital: A view showing the southern side of the Morge Baild.
ing; which is located at the S.E. corner of First Ave., and East 29th Street.
February 4, 1937.
W.P.A. Photo.
City Wide Project.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.

711911f.title: Manhattan: 29th Street (East) - 1st Avenue
711911f.text:
The old Morgue, 40O East 29th Street,at S. E. corner of First
Avenue. This will be replaced by a six story building.
About 1905.
May be reproduced.

711909f-a.text:
29th Street, south side, east of First Avenue, with a clearing
on the north side, showing the Bellevue Hospital laundry and
other buildinga.
April 27, 1930.
L. Sperr.  P. 1
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

711912f-a.title: Manhattan: 29th Street - 1st Avenue
711912f-a.text:
Fidelio Brewery, 29th Street at, adjoining and west of the N.W.
corner of First Avenue. The S.W. corner of First avenue and
29th Street is shown at the left.
April 31, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

711908f-a.title: Manhattan: 29th Street (East) - 1st Avenue
711908f-a.text:
29th Street, south side, west from 330 East 29th, west of First
Avenue. In the left centre is the parochial school of the
Carmelite Roman Catholic Church.
June 24, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
